title: The Tent Restaurant (Al-Khaimah) - Nouakchott
reviews/2/textTranslated: absurd
reviews/4/text:
The Tent Restaurant (Al-Khaimah) in Nouakchott is an establishment you should avoid like the plague. If you have even a shred of regard for your time, steer clear of this place. Our experience was nothing short of a nightmare.

After waiting for an hour for our food, we were informed that they didn't have what we ordered. Fine, mistakes happen, right? Wrong. After changing our order, they returned ten minutes later to inform us that they didn't have that either, but miraculously had the original order available now. Unbelievable.

To compound the frustration, our drink orders were repeatedly botched. Despite multiple attempts to rectify the situation, they consistently brought the wrong drinks. When we finally managed to catch their attention, we were met with an aggressive, rude, and shockingly racist manager. Their behavior was utterly disgraceful, and they even went as far as to hurl insults and demand we leave the premises.

As if that wasn't enough, when we dared to express our dissatisfaction, the manager threatened to call the police, accusing us of wasting their money despite our honest attempts to rectify their mistakes. It was a complete circus, and the final straw was when the manager tried to twist the situation, claiming that we had sworn at them and called them names, which was entirely false. They even had the audacity to tell us, "Go back to your country and order the juice there. This is Mauritania and this is how we make the juice."

In summary, The Tent Restaurant is a cesspool of incompetence, disrespect, and racism. Save yourself the trouble and dine elsewhere.

********

Le Restaurant The Tent (Al-Khaimah) à Nouakchott est un établissement à éviter à tout prix. Si vous avez le moindre respect pour votre temps, éloignez-vous de cet endroit. Notre expérience n'était rien de moins qu'un cauchemar.

Après avoir attendu une heure pour notre nourriture, on nous a informés qu'ils n'avaient pas ce que nous avions commandé. Bon, les erreurs arrivent, n'est-ce pas ? Faux. Après avoir changé notre commande, ils sont revenus dix minutes plus tard pour nous informer qu'ils n'avaient pas non plus cela, mais qu'ils avaient miraculeusement la commande originale disponible maintenant. Incroyable.

Pour aggraver la frustration, nos commandes de boissons étaient constamment bâclées. Malgré plusieurs tentatives pour rectifier la situation, ils apportaient systématiquement les mauvaises boissons. Lorsque nous avons enfin réussi à attirer leur attention, nous avons été confrontés à un manager agressif, impoli et choquant de racisme. Leur comportement était totalement honteux, et ils sont même allés jusqu'à proférer des insultes et exiger que nous quittions les lieux.

Comme si cela ne suffisait pas, lorsque nous avons osé exprimer notre insatisfaction, le manager a menacé d'appeler la police, nous accusant de gaspiller leur argent malgré nos tentatives honnêtes de rectifier leurs erreurs. C'était un vrai cirque, et le comble a été lorsque le manager a essayé de déformer la situation, prétendant que nous les avions insultés et traités de noms, ce qui était totalement faux. Ils ont même eu l'audace de nous dire : "Retournez dans votre pays et commandez le jus là-bas. C'est la Mauritanie et c'est ainsi que nous faisons le jus."

En résumé, le Restaurant The Tent est un foyer d'incompétence, de manque de respect et de racisme. Épargnez-vous les ennuis et allez dîner ailleurs.

title: Tata joyce
reviews/1/text: Le restaurant Tata Joyce, spécialisé dans la cuisine nigériane et ghanéenne, offre une expérience culinaire authentique et savoureuse. Les plats sont préparés avec des ingrédients frais et des épices traditionnelles, offrant une explosion de saveurs en bouche. L'ambiance est chaleureuse et conviviale, idéale pour découvrir les spécialités de ces deux pays. Le service est généralement rapide et attentionné, rendant l'expérience agréable. Les portions sont généreuses, et les prix raisonnables, ce qui en fait un excellent rapport qualité-prix.
reviews/1/textTranslated: Tata Joyce Restaurant, specializing in Nigerian and Ghanaian cuisine, offers an authentic and flavorful dining experience. The dishes are prepared with fresh ingredients and traditional spices, offering an explosion of flavors in the mouth. The atmosphere is warm and friendly, ideal for discovering the specialties of these two countries. Service is generally fast and attentive, making the experience enjoyable. The portions are generous, and the prices reasonable, making it excellent value for money.
reviews/2/textTranslated: Very good

title: THE BAKERY
reviews/0/text: Vous étiez bien super même, mais dernièrement vous commencez à relâcher dans le mauvais sens
reviews/0/textTranslated: You used to be great, but lately you're starting to let go in the wrong way.
reviews/2/text:
J'ai fait la commande de menu kids pour les enfants et sincèrement je recommande.
Composé d'un mini burger, nuggets, frites, caprisun, yaourt a boire, chocolat et jouet les enfants étaient ravie !
J'ai également commander un menu egg burger qui était délicieux, surtout la sauce, beaucoup de frite. Attention cependant à la cuisson du steak qui était un peu noir.
En dessert, la crêpe Dubaï étai décevante. Très grosse crêpe pour 2 voir 3 personnes mais très épaisse pour au final un manque de garniture a mon goût. Le dessert Lotus n'est pas extraordinaire, beaucoup de ganache blanche sans goût particulier.
Nous avons pris a emporter.
Quand les enfants sont contents, les adultes sont moins critiques 😉
Je recommande pour les menus enfants et les burger.
Ps : j'ai galéré à trouver le menu en amont, surtout pour une grosse commande ou bien quand on veut en livraison donc je vous le partage ici.
Bon appétit 🤗
reviews/2/textTranslated:
I ordered the kids menu for the children and I sincerely recommend it.
Composed of a mini burger, nuggets, fries, caprisun, yogurt drink, chocolate and toy, the children were delighted!
I also ordered an egg burger menu which was delicious, especially the sauce, lots of fries. Be careful, however, with the cooking of the steak which was a little black.
For dessert, the Dubai crepe was disappointing. Very large crepe for 2 or even 3 people but very thick resulting in a lack of filling for my taste. The Lotus dessert is not extraordinary, a lot of white ganache with no particular taste.
We took takeaway.
When children are happy, adults are less critical 😉
I recommend for children's menus and burgers.
Ps: I struggled to find the menu in advance, especially for a large order or when you want delivery, so I'm sharing it with you here.
Enjoy your meal 🤗

The restaurant is classic in terms of design and is suitable for small get-togethers and gatherings in general, and many young people use it as a suitable place to watch football matches, but their food is normal from my point of view. I tried the tea, and it came cold, in addition to the lack of sugar. They served us fried chicken, but I prefer it grilled. However, it is rumored that a group of secularists and atheists often gather in it, and you can sometimes find well-dressed women and card players...
But in general, it is considered ideal for drinking tea and coffee, which is why it is called café Tunisie. It is worth noting that it contains a prayer hall for those who want to pray, and this is a good step.

title: The Hummingbird Restaurant
reviews/0/text: Wonderful French restaurant, good food , good life
reviews/1/text:
Dernière visite au resto, une horreur ! Je prends un petit-déjeuner et au préalable j'avais vu sa composition. Déjà on m'apporte une bouteille d'eau avec un bouchon mal en point. Je fais la remarque et la serveuse était soûlée de revenir sur ses pas pour me chercher une autre bouteille. À mon arrivée pas d'acceuil chaleureux et l'une des serveuses n'avait d'yeux que pour son téléphone derrière le bar...

On me ramène pas de beurre, pas de venoisseries sans explications. Je me lève pour comprendre on me dit "on peut vous ramenez du beurre" non ! C'est pas comme je veux, c'est compris dans la formule... Et pour les venoisseries, on me dit que pendant le Ramadan y en a pas. Explication pas claire du tout. Je fais remarquer à la serveuse son comportement pas pro, zéro communication avec le client, je lui parle et elle a un l'air limite désinvolte, le ton monte un peu.

Je suis en terrasse et c'était horrible. Trop de mouches et de moustiques et aucune disposition du resto pour améliorer mon confort. J'ai fait exprès de ne rien dire et ben mon confort n'était pas leur problème.

On me ramène une omelette, un gateau à l'orange (j'avais pas demandé ce gâteau en plus), avec du miel et du labé pas compris dans la formule mais pareil zéro explication. La salade de fruit n'était pas fraîche, les fruits étaient un peu défraîchis et beaucoup d'eau se trouvaient au fond de la coupole

Au moment de payer grosse déception de la gérante avec qui j'ai eu à échanger plusieurs fois pour mes précédentes visites au resto. Zéro geste commercial, j'ai payé plein pot pour une formule mangé à moitié. Elle s'est juste contenter d'un "je suis désolée" et le comble en partant elle me rappelle pour me faire la promo des réseaux sociaux du resto. Quelle énorme maladresse 😮

Ps : j'ai attendu qques jours avant de poster ce message pour savoir si le resto allait me contacter pour se rattraper, mais RIEN.
Vous venez de perdre une habituée. En un mois de présence dans la ville, cette mauvaise expérience était mon 3e passage et du coup mon dernier au Colibri.

Ps 2 : je viens de recevoir d'une ami, votre flyer de votre menu spéciale aux saveurs d'Asie de jeudi 3 avril
reviews/1/textTranslated:
Last visit to the restaurant, a horror! I have breakfast and beforehand I had seen its composition. Already someone brings me a bottle of water with a damaged cap. I made the remark and the waitress was drunk to come back and get me another bottle. When I arrived there was no warm welcome and one of the waitresses only had eyes for her phone behind the bar...

They don't bring me any butter, or any venison without explanation. I get up to understand, they tell me “we can bring you some butter” no! It's not what I want, it's included in the formula... And as for venoisseries, I'm told that during Ramadan there aren't any. Explanation not clear at all. I point out to the waitress her unprofessional behavior, zero communication with the customer, I speak to her and she seems borderline casual, her tone rises a little.

I'm on the terrace and it was horrible. Too many flies and mosquitoes and no provisions in the restaurant to improve my comfort. I purposely didn't say anything and well, my comfort wasn't their problem.

They bring me an omelette, an orange cake (I hadn't asked for this extra cake), with honey and labé not included in the formula but the same zero explanation. The fruit salad was not fresh, the fruit was a little stale and there was a lot of water at the bottom of the dome

When paying, big disappointment from the manager with whom I had to communicate several times during my previous visits to the restaurant. Zero commercial gesture, I paid full price for a formula I ate half. She just said "I'm sorry" and to top it off, when she left, she called me back to promote the restaurant's social networks. What a huge clumsiness 😮

Ps: I waited a few days before posting this message to find out if the restaurant would contact me to make up for it, but NOTHING.
You just lost a regular. In a month of being in the city, this bad experience was my 3rd visit and therefore my last at the Colibri.

Ps 2: I have just received from a friend, your flyer for your special menu with Asian flavors for Thursday, April 3

title: Tafarit Restaurant
reviews/1/text: One of the best sea food restaurants
reviews/2/text:
Harika deniz ürünleri. Izgara balik ve diğer deniz ürünleri o kadar lezizdi ki her akşam Tafarit restorana gittim. Et urunlerini denemedim ancak onlarin da guzel olduğunu düşünüyorum. Kesinlikle tek geçtiğim bir lezzet merkezi. WiFi yok. Kredi karti alınmıyor.

31 Mayıs ziyaretimde bazi değişiklikleri fark ettim.  Öncelikle ve malesef yemek kalitesi çok fazla düşmüş. Jumbo karides ( Gambas) siparişi vermemem rağmen bildiğiniz küçük karides getirildi. Deniz ürünleri restoranlarda şef çok önemlidir.  Acaba ızgara yapan sef mi degisti bilemiyorum.  Lokantanın eski günlerine dönmesini temenni ediyorum.
reviews/2/textTranslated:
Great seafood. Grilled fish and other seafood were so delicious that I went to Tafarit restaurant every evening. I didn't try the meat products but I think they were also delicious. It's definitely a flavor center that I only go to. No WiFi. No credit cards.

I noticed some changes during my May 31 visit. First of all, and unfortunately, the quality of the food has dropped a lot. Although I didn't order jumbo shrimp (Gambas), they brought small shrimp. The chef is very important in seafood restaurants. I don't know if the chef who does the grilling has changed. I hope the restaurant returns to its old days.
reviews/5/text: This restaurant was located not far from our hotel accommodation so we went here with my colleagues for dinner. At 19:00 the place is not very crowded as the locals prefer to dine later. Menu is in French and Arabic so we were bit stragling with translation but our waiter could speak Spanish so we managed to place order...Food arrived in good time and we were pleased with our choices of fishes, most of us ordered octopus witch was fresh and tasted so delicious.. portions were fair my colleague even could not finish her meal so they prepared take away from it...we payed cash, the prices were higher then expected but overall nice experience and we can only recommend for those who like fish and seafood dishes.

title: Restaurant Elzhar
reviews/3/text:
أعجبتني اطباقة التي تشبه الأطباق البديله للأكل النباتي

فهناك العديد من البدائل النباتية اللذيذة والمفيدة. إليك خمسًا منها:

1. **التوفو**: مصنوع من حليب الصويا المكثف، ويعتبر بديلًا جيدًا للبروتينات الحيوانية في العديد من الأطباق.
2. **التيمبيه**: مصنوع من فول الصويا المخمر، ويحتوي على نكهة قوية وقوام رائع يمكن استخدامه في القلي أو الشواء.
3. **البرغر النباتي**: تُصنع من الخضروات، الحبوب، والفاصوليا، وتُقدم بديلًا شهيًا للبرغر التقليدي.
4. **الحليب النباتي**: يشمل حليب اللوز، الشوفان، والأرز، وهذه الأنواع تعتبر بدائل ممتازة للحليب البقري.
5. **جبن الكاجو**: يُصنع من الكاجو ويعطي نكهة مميزة وملمسًا كريميًا رائعًا يُستخدم في الطهي أو كسطح لوجبات الخبز.
reviews/3/textTranslated:
I liked the dishes that resemble alternative dishes for plant-based foods.

There are many delicious and healthy plant-based alternatives. Here are five of them:

1. **Tofu**: Made from condensed soy milk, it's a good substitute for animal proteins in many dishes.
2. **Tempeh**: Made from fermented soybeans, it has a strong flavor and a wonderful texture that can be used in frying or grilling.
3. **Vegan Burgers**: Made from vegetables, grains, and beans, they offer a delicious alternative to traditional burgers.
4. **Plant-Based Milk**: These include almond, oat, and rice milks, and are excellent alternatives to cow's milk.
5. **Cashew Cheese**: Made from cashews, it gives a distinctive flavor and a wonderful creamy texture that's great for cooking or as a topping for baked goods.
reviews/4/text: The food really changed my life. The was the crispy bread sunk around my teeth was something else. Big elzhar himself even made an appearance and was happy to sign all my memorabilia. 5/5 my life’s been changed forever.

title: Saveurs D'Italie
reviews/4/text:
J'avais eu de très bons échos pourtant. Alors je décide pour tester, de prendre leurs mignardises pour le mois de Ramadan. Pas beaucoup de monde et les 2 serveuses semblaient dépassées. Un client s'énerve et part. À mon tour, je choisis mes produits et au moment de ma rupture grosse déception. C'était très salées, les feuilles de bricks trop imbibées d'huile, les croquettes de fromage trop écœurante en raison de l'excédent de sel.

À part les 2 parts de pizzas, le cheesecake Lotus, les bricks et les croquettes ont fini à la poubelle 😭
reviews/4/textTranslated:
However, I had very good feedback. So I decide to test, to take their sweet treats for the month of Ramadan. Not many people and the 2 waitresses seemed overwhelmed. A customer gets angry and leaves. In my turn, I choose my products and when I break up, I am very disappointed. It was very salty, the brick sheets too soaked in oil, the cheese croquettes too disgusting due to the excess salt.

Apart from the 2 slices of pizza, the Lotus cheesecake, the bricks and the croquettes ended up in the trash 😭

أنا عربي وفي بلد عربي. ولا أحد في المطعم قادر على التحدث بالعربية! ولا حتى إنجليزية.
إما تتحدث لغة المستعمر الفرنسي الذي استقلت موريتانيا منه من 65 سنة أو لا نستطيع خدمتك! أمر معيب.
reviews/7/textTranslated:
The first time I arrived at the restaurant, I thought the map was wrong, because there were no signs or landmarks of a restaurant on the street.

When I entered the second time,
I am Arab and in an Arab country. No one in the restaurant is able to speak Arabic! Not even English.
Either you speak the language of the French colonialists from whom Mauritania gained independence 65 years ago, or we cannot serve you! Defective.

reviews/2/text:
معلومة قصيرة عن المشوي

المشوي في المطبخ العربي هو كل ما يشوى من لحم الأغنام أو الضأن من الأحسن على الفحم، وهي كلمة عربية من الفعل "شوى"، ويحظى هذا الطبق بشعبية كبيرة في الوطن العربي وبلدان أخرى مثل إيران وباكستان، ويمكن أن تستخدم كل أنواع اللحوم للشوي ومن أمثلتها شيش طاووق (بلحم الدجاج).

" مطاعم انواكشوط بنكهة عربية

وقد ازدحمت العاصمة الموريتانية نواكشوط بالمطاعم العربية بشكل لافت لدرجة أن البعض أصبح يطلق عليها بالظاهرة التي تستحق الدراسة. وتشير التقارير إلى أن 90% من العرب الموجودين في موريتانيا يديرون مطاعم وفنادق تقدم لأهل نواكشوط مختلف النكهات العربية.

"
reviews/2/textTranslated:
Short information about grilled meat

Grilled, in Arabic cuisine, is anything that is grilled from sheep or lamb meat, preferably over charcoal. It is an Arabic word from the verb “shwa”, and this dish is very popular in the Arab world and other countries such as Iran and Pakistan. All types of meat can be used for grilling, an example of which is Shish Tawouk (with chicken meat).

“Nouakchott restaurants with an Arabic flavour

The Mauritanian capital, Nouakchott, has become remarkably crowded with Arab restaurants, to the point that some have come to call it a phenomenon worthy of study. Reports indicate that 90% of the Arabs in Mauritania run restaurants and hotels that provide the people of Nouakchott with various Arabic flavors.

"

reviews/4/text:
مطاعم نواكشوط بنكهة عربية

ازدحمت العاصمة الموريتانية نواكشوط بالمطاعم العربية بشكل لافت لدرجة أن البعض أصبح يطلق عليها بالظاهرة التي تستحق الدراسة. وتشير التقارير إلى أن 90% من العرب الموجودين في موريتانيا يديرون مطاعم وفنادق تقدم لأهل نواكشوط مختلف النكهات العربية.
reviews/4/textTranslated:
Nouakchott restaurants with an Arabic flavour

The Mauritanian capital, Nouakchott, has become remarkably crowded with Arab restaurants, to the point that some have come to call it a phenomenon worthy of study. Reports indicate that 90% of the Arabs in Mauritania run restaurants and hotels that provide the people of Nouakchott with various Arabic flavors.

لا انصح بزيارته.
reviews/4/textTranslated:
Arkan Cafe, opposite the Moroccan Embassy in Nouakchott, had very poor service, was dirty, played very loud and loud music as if we were a nightclub, and did not listen to the customers’ requests to reduce it. We were almost screaming to listen to each other, and when we asked for light Moroccan tea, they offered us Mauritanian tea with an unknown, bad-tasting “warg,” and they refused to change or replace it.
I do not recommend visiting it.

title: Healthy Corner Restaurant | مطعم الركن الصحي
reviews/0/text:
I came for breakfast twice with my wife, we love it.
It’s different from the standard breakfast options here in Nouakchott.
reviews/1/responseFromOwnerText: Thank you for sharing your feedback. We're truly sorry to hear that your experience with us was not up to expectations. Our orange juice is freshly pressed to order, but if it didn’t meet your taste, we’d be happy to offer a replacement. We also offer +10 different breakfast options, so we hope there is something you can enjoy on your next visit. We value your comments and are committed to improving based on your experience. We hope to have the opportunity to welcome you again soon.
reviews/1/text:
The breakfast options were very limited, and the food itself was disappointing. The orange served was not fresh and appeared rotten, which raises concerns about food safety. The hot chocolate was the worst I’ve ever had – completely lacking in flavor and warmth. Overall, this was the least enjoyable breakfast I’ve had in the city.

I hope improvements are made soon, as this experience did not live up to the reputation.
reviews/4/text: Best and safest restaurant/coffee in the town, the concept is about healthy food, it is clean, cold, and the staff are friendly.
reviews/6/text: They are the best corner in nouakchott, the stuff is kind and welcoming, can’t wait to visit them again.
reviews/7/text: C’est le pire service qui a m’a été présenté depuis que j’habite en Mauritanie. On a passé 1 heure à attendre notre commande, dans la chaleur car la clim ne marchait pas. Une fois que la commande est arrivée la nourriture n’était pas bonne, le café mal fait, les viennoiseries étaient dures comme si elles avaient été chauffées au micro-onde, et le pancake n’était également pas bon. Si vous voulez passer un bon temps je ne vous conseille pas du tout de manger ici.
reviews/7/textTranslated: This is the worst service that has been presented to me since I lived in Mauritania. We spent 1 hour waiting for our order, in the heat because the air conditioning didn't work. Once the order arrived the food was not good, the coffee was poorly made, the pastries were hard as if they had been heated in the microwave, and the pancake was also not good. If you want to have a good time I don't recommend eating here at all.
reviews/8/text: Thanks health corner nice food keep going
